issue.title: Problem of rounding off figures in stock

labels.name: Severity: Normal
labels.description: Bugs which have an acceptable workaround. Moderate/tolerable user impact. Next minor release.

issue.body: ## What went wrong? 😲 There is a decimal problem in the stock display. The first screen shoot shows a quantity of 6.800000000000001. ![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5861f95f-0b09-4bcf-9f0a-0fd8a50fac2f) The second shows a quantity of 19.099999999999994. I think this happens after a dose of vaccine is delivered in the dispensary (but not for all vaccines and after every dispensation). ## Expected behaviour 🤔 Rounding must be to the second decimal place. ## How to Reproduce 🔨 Steps to reproduce the behaviour: 1. Dispense a new dose in Dispensary. (choose a Patient, add an encounter in the past, save and click on one vaccine to dispense, Dispense it) 2. Go to 'Inventory', 'View Stock' 3. The error is not found for all vaccines and for all dispensations. ## Your environment 🌱 - Open mSupply Version: 2.6.00 Demo - Legacy mSupply Central Server Version: N/A - Platform: Mac - Database type: @richardmoizeau

comment.body:
Requires further investigation and we are prioritising 2.8.0 work atm, so will unassign myself.
It seem there are are two issues at play:
1. Wierd numbers need to display properly (believe fixed in original PR)
2. How are wierd numbers being generated anyway (requires investigation)
Unsure whether to make a new issue for the second one as it seems to be relevant to this one.
